---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import DaysUntilImX from '../components/DaysUntilImX.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="How Many Days Until I'm X — Age Milestone Countdown | Clockr"
	description="Find out exactly when you'll reach any age. Countdown to 18, 21, 30, 40, 50, 65 or any target age in years, months and days."
	category="birthdays"
>
	<div class="duix-page">
		<div class="duix-header">
			<div class="duix-eyebrow">
				<span class="duix-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				AGE & BIRTHDAYS
			</div>
			<h1 class="duix-title">
				<span class="duix-gradient">How Many Days Until I'm...</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="duix-subtitle">
				Find out exactly when you'll reach any age
			</p>
		</div>

		<DaysUntilImX client:load />

		<section class="duix-how">
			<h2 class="duix-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="duix-how-card">
				<p>
					People look up future age milestones for all sorts of reasons. Legal
					thresholds like turning 18 or 21 matter for voting, driving, and
					drinking in different countries. Round-number birthdays — 30, 40, 50,
					65 — prompt reflection and celebration. Others simply want to plan a
					party, book time off work, or satisfy curiosity about when a specific
					age arrives on the calendar.
				</p>
				<p>
					Enter your birth date and a target age, and Clockr calculates the
					exact calendar date on which you reach that age. For whole-number
					ages, the tool adds that many years to your date of birth — so someone
					born on 14 March 2000 turns 30 on 14 March 2030. The countdown from
					today is broken into years, months, and days, accounting for months of
					different lengths and leap years. You can also enter fractional ages
					like 21.5 for a half-birthday, which adds six months after the full
					years.
				</p>
				<p>
					Milestone birthdays hold a special place in many cultures. Eighteen
					marks adulthood in the UK; twenty-one is a classic coming-of-age in the
					US; thirty, forty, and fifty are decades people often celebrate with
					parties or trips; and sixty-five has long been associated with
					retirement. Round numbers feel significant because they give us a clear
					marker on life's timeline — even though every birthday is, strictly
					speaking, just one more day.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="duix-faq">
			<h2 class="duix-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="duix-faq-list">
				<details class="duix-faq-item">
					<summary class="duix-faq-question"
						>How do I find out what date I'll turn a certain age?</summary
					>
					<div class="duix-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter your date of birth and the age you want to reach. Clockr
							adds that many years to your birth date and shows the exact
							calendar date, plus a countdown in years, months, and days from
							today. For example, if you were born on 5 June 1995 and enter
							30, the result is 5 June 2025.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="duix-faq-item">
					<summary class="duix-faq-question"
						>What date will I turn 18, 21, or 30?</summary
					>
					<div class="duix-faq-answer">
						<p>
							It depends on your birth date. Someone born on 1 January 2008
							turns 18 on 1 January 2026; someone born on 15 August 2005 turns
							21 on 15 August 2026. Use the quick-link buttons for 18, 21,
							30, 40, 50, or 65 to populate the target age instantly, or type
							any age you like.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="duix-faq-item">
					<summary class="duix-faq-question"
						>Can I find out when I'll be a specific age in the past?</summary
					>
					<div class="duix-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. If the target age has already passed, Clockr shows when you
							turned that age and how many days ago it was, rather than a
							negative countdown. For example, if you are 35 and enter 30, you
							will see the date you turned 30 and the number of days since
							then.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="duix-faq-item">
					<summary class="duix-faq-question"
						>What day of the week will my birthday fall on in the future?</summary
					>
					<div class="duix-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr displays the day of the week for your milestone date
							below the countdown. Because your birthday falls on the same
							calendar date each year, the weekday shifts by one or two days
							annually (and by two days across a leap year boundary), cycling
							through all seven days over time.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="duix-faq-item">
					<summary class="duix-faq-question"
						>How accurate is this calculation?</summary
					>
					<div class="duix-faq-answer">
						<p>
							For whole-number ages, Clockr adds years directly to your birth
							date — the same method used for legal age in most countries. The
							countdown uses calendar arithmetic that respects varying month
							lengths and leap years. It counts full calendar days from today to
							the milestone date, so the result matches standard date-difference
							calculations.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>

				<details class="duix-faq-item">
					<summary class="duix-faq-question"
						>Can I calculate half-birthdays or fractional ages?</summary
					>
					<div class="duix-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. Enter a decimal age like 21.5 and Clockr treats the
							fractional part as additional months — 0.5 equals six months after
							the full years. This is useful for half-birthday celebrations or
							any milestone that falls between two birthdays. Whole numbers
							remain the primary use case and are what most legal age thresholds
							rely on.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="duix-related">
			<h3 class="duix-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="duix-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="duix-related-card"
					><span class="duix-related-name">Age Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-birthday" class="duix-related-card"
					><span class="duix-related-name">Days Until Birthday</span></a
				>
				<a href="/retirement-countdown-calculator" class="duix-related-card"
					><span class="duix-related-name">Retirement Countdown Calculator</span
					></a
				>
				<a href="/life-in-numbers" class="duix-related-card"
					><span class="duix-related-name">Your Life in Numbers</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.duix-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.duix-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.duix-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.duix-eyebrow-square {
		width: 10px;
		height: 10px;
		border-radius: 3px;
		background: #8b5cf6;
		box-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.35);
	}

	.duix-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.duix-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.duix-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.duix-tool) {
		margin-bottom: 56px;
	}

	:global(.duix-card) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.duix-inputs) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 18px;
	}

	:global(.duix-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.duix-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.duix-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.duix-input::placeholder) {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	:global(.duix-input--number) {
		-moz-appearance: textfield;
	}

	:global(.duix-input--number::-webkit-outer-spin-button),
	:global(.duix-input--number::-webkit-inner-spin-button) {
		-webkit-appearance: none;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.duix-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
	}

	:global(.duix-presets) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.duix-presets-title) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.duix-presets-grid) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 10px;
	}

	:global(.duix-preset) {
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.22);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
	}

	:global(.duix-preset:hover) {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.45);
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.08);
	}

	:global(.duix-results) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 50px rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.06);
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.duix-main) {
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.duix-main-heading) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1.5px;
		line-height: 1.2;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.duix-countdown) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 20px;
	}

	:global(.duix-countdown-item) {
		background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.18);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 18px 12px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 6px;
	}

	:global(.duix-countdown-num) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	:global(.duix-countdown-label) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.35);
	}

	:global(.duix-total-days) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		margin: 0 0 12px;
	}

	:global(.duix-weekday) {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(.duix-past-note) {
		background: rgba(236, 72, 153, 0.05);
		border-left: 3px solid #ec4899;
		border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;
		padding: 14px 18px;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		line-height: 1.6;
		text-align: left;
		margin: 16px 0 0;
	}

	.duix-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.duix-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.duix-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.duix-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.duix-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.duix-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.duix-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.duix-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.duix-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.duix-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.duix-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.duix-faq-item[open] .duix-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.duix-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.duix-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.duix-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.duix-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.duix-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.duix-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.duix-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.4);
	}

	.duix-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8b5cf6, #ec4899);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.duix-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		:global(.duix-main-heading) {
			font-size: 26px;
		}

		:global(.duix-countdown) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		:global(.duix-presets-grid) {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}

		.duix-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
